						</paratext>
						<eop/>
					</para>
				</footnote.body>
			</footnote>
			<footnote ID="I7972ce7274d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">
				<label.designator>3</label.designator>
				<footnote.body>
					<para>
						<bop/>
						<bos/>
						<paratext>
							<cite.query w-src-number="0287017149" w-serial-number="1962116387" w-seq-number="00008" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000350" ID="If35e9e4174d211eab2f0b920da2605c5">U.S. v. 2,872.88 Acres of Land, More or Less, in Clay and Quitman Counties, State of Ga., 310 F.2d 775 (5th Cir. 1962)</cite.query>, <case.history>judgment modified</case.history>, <cite.query w-src-number="0287017149" w-serial-number="1964105788" w-seq-number="00009" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000708" ID="If35e9e4474d211eab2f0b920da2605c5">376 U.S. 192, 84 S. Ct. 639, 11 L. Ed. 2d 629 (1964)</cite.query>.<eos/>
						</paratext>
						<eop/>
					</para>
				</footnote.body>
			</footnote>
			<footnote ID="I7972f58074d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">
				<label.designator>4</label.designator>
				<footnote.body>
					<para>
						<bop/>
						<bos/>
						<paratext>See <cite.query w-src-number="0287017149" w-seq-number="00010" w-ref-type="LQ" w-normalized-cite="GAST24-7-701" w-pub-number="1000468" ID="If35f137074d211eab2f0b920da2605c5">O.C.G.A. § 24-7-701(b)</cite.query>, which provides:</paratext>
						<display.quote>
							<para>
								<paratext>
									<begin.quote ID="QT_0002"/>Direct testimony as to market value is in the nature of opinion evidence. <eos/>
									<bos/>A witness need not be an expert or dealer in the article or property to testify as to its value if he or she has had an opportunity to form a reasoned opinion.<eos/>
									<end.quote refid="QT_0002"/>
								</paratext>
							</para>
						</display.quote>
						<eop/>
					</para>
					<para>
						<bop/>
						<bos/>
						<paratext>Also see <cite.query w-src-number="0287017149" w-seq-number="00011" w-ref-type="LQ" w-normalized-cite="GAST22-1-14" w-pub-number="1000468" ID="If35fafb074d211eab2f0b920da2605c5">O.C.G.A. § 22-1-14</cite.query>, providing that, when property is condemned, <begin.quote ID="QT_0001"/>“the value of the condemned property may be determined through lay or expert testimony and its admissibility shall be addressed to the sound discretion of the court.”<eos/>
							<end.quote refid="QT_0001"/>
						</paratext>
						<eop/>
					</para>
				</footnote.body>
			</footnote>
			<footnote ID="I7972f58174d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">
				<label.designator>5</label.designator>
				<footnote.body>
					<para>
						<bop/>
						<bos/>
						<paratext>
							<cite.query w-src-number="0287017149" w-serial-number="1976135553" w-seq-number="00012" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000711" ID="If360c12274d211eab2f0b920da2605c5">White v. Georgia Power Co., 237 Ga. 341, 227 S.E.2d 385 (1976)</cite.query> (<case.history>overruled on other grounds by</case.history>, <cite.query w-src-number="0287017149" w-serial-number="1979144357" w-seq-number="00013" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000711" ID="If360c12574d211eab2f0b920da2605c5">DeKalb County v. Trustees, Decatur Lodge No. 1602, B. P. O. Elks, 242 Ga. 707, 251 S.E.2d 243 (1978)</cite.query>).<eos/>
						</paratext>
						<eop/>
					</para>
					<para>
						<bop/>
						<bos/>
						<paratext>See also <cite.query w-src-number="0287017149" w-serial-number="1977114107" w-seq-number="00014" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000711" ID="If3610f4274d211eab2f0b920da2605c5">Slenker v. Department of Transp., 141 Ga. App. 504, 233 S.E.2d 871 (1977)</cite.query>.<eos/>
						</paratext>
						<eop/>
